### Pollution Tracker API — manual test requests
### Requires the "REST Client" VS Code extension (recommended in .vscode/extensions.json)
### Click "Send Request" above any request below to run it.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000

### Health check — confirms the API is up
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### Root — shows whether Gemini is in MOCK or LIVE mode
GET {{baseUrl}}/

### ---------------------------------------------------------------
### CORE LOOP: upload -> classify -> cluster -> score
### ---------------------------------------------------------------

### Create a report (citizen upload). 
### The # @name tag allows us to grab the response variables later!
# @name createReport
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/reports
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary123

--boundary123
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="latitude"

17.385044
--boundary123
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="longitude"

78.486671
--boundary123
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="description"

Garbage pile near main road, test via REST Client
--boundary123
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="photo"; filename="test.jpg"
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< ./test-assets/sample-photo.jpg
--boundary123--


### Automatically grab the cluster_id from the creation step above
@clusterId = {{createReport.response.body.cluster_id}}


### List all clusters, ranked by severity (this is what the dashboard should call)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/reports/clusters

### Filter clusters by status
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/reports/clusters?status=pending

### Get a single cluster by ID (Uses dynamic variable)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/reports/clusters/{{clusterId}}

### Get all individual reports that make up a cluster (Uses dynamic variable)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/reports/clusters/{{clusterId}}/reports

### Update a cluster's status (Pending -> Assigned -> Resolved)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/reports/clusters/{{clusterId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "assigned"
}

### ---------------------------------------------------------------
### BEFORE/AFTER VERIFICATION (Day 3 differentiator feature)
### ---------------------------------------------------------------

### Submit an "after" photo to verify a cluster is resolved
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/verification/clusters/{{clusterId}}/verify
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary456

--boundary456
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="after_photo"; filename="after.jpg"
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< ./test-assets/sample-photo-after.jpg
--boundary456--

### ---------------------------------------------------------------
### VALIDATION / ERROR CASES — useful for confirming things fail correctly
### ---------------------------------------------------------------

### Should return 422: latitude out of range
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/reports
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary789

--boundary789
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="latitude"

200
--boundary789
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="longitude"

78.5
--boundary789
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="photo"; filename="test.jpg"
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< ./test-assets/sample-photo.jpg
--boundary789--

### Should return 404: cluster doesn't exist
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/reports/clusters/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
